        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 11:14PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1114 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Wayside, or 22 miles south of Claude, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Wayside and Goodnight.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
